The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 June is 43,046 (4,982.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 June, there were 292 new confirmed cases (33.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 June, there were 252 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 16% (40 extra cases).
